/*
Each line still defines a character with a set of x and y coordinates.
The origin (0, 0) for each character is a reference point for rendering,
often placed at the character's base.

The x and y coordinates are scaled to fit within a 1.0 by 1.0 grid
(from -0.5 to 0.5 in a centered style,
 or from 0.0 to 1.0 in a bottom-left aligned style).

This example uses a bottom-left aligned style for easier positioning.
(0,1)                       (1,1)
      .--------------------.
      |                    |
      |                    |
      |                    |
      |                    |
      |                    |
      |                    |
(0,0) .--------------------. (1,0)  +X

*/
